    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="925"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-12T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 12, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3913. From Spalding<note n="73" xml:id="d925fn1">Brig. Gen. Sidney P. Spalding,
                        Chief of the Supply Division, United States Military Mission to the Soviet
                        Union.</note> to SPC,<note n="74" xml:id="d925fn2">Presumably the Government
                        Purchasing Commission of the Soviet Union in the United States.</note>
                        Wesson<note n="75" xml:id="d925fn3">Maj. Gen. Charles M. Wesson, Director,
                        Division for Soviet Supply, Foreign Economic Administration.</note> and to
                    the Department for information. General Fleming is returning to the United
                    States after a very successful trip here. He has visited Dnieperstroi,<note
                        n="76" xml:id="d925fn4">Dneprostroy was the huge hydro-electrical power
                        station and dam on the Dnepr River near Zaporozhe.</note> Stalino and
                    Leningrad and has discussed reconstruction and housing. Suggest that you can
                    obtain valuable and authoritative information from him in connection with
                    lend-lease problems. Soviet authorities especially foreign trade have been most
                    helpful and cooperative in arranging his visit. [Spalding.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
